==Reporting back to Brother Tranquility==
* '''Brother Tranquility:''' So, have you found anything out about the pirates' plans?
* '''Player:''' The pirates are planning on using some sort of sleeping gas to knock you all out!
* '''Player:''' When everyone is unconscious, they are going to come in and take you away for brain-swaps!
* '''Brother Tranquility:''' Fiendish!
* '''Brother Tranquility:''' We have to prepare our defence against this threat. I recall something that might well help...
* '''Player:''' Is it some sort of potion to counteract the poison?
* '''Brother Tranquility:''' No, no. You see, the gas will work on us faster than a normal poison, and a potion would take too long to diffuse through the stomach. 
* '''Brother Tranquility:''' No, what I'm thinking of is a prayer written centuries ago by one of the abbots at the Edgeville Monastery.
* '''Brother Tranquility:''' protected.
* '''Player:''' Hmm, how come I've never heard of this prayer?
* '''Brother Tranquility:''' Well, the abbot was slain by a group of raiders. Apparently his faith was little protection against their repeated sword blows.
* '''Player:''' Ouch!
* '''Brother Tranquility:''' Anyway, the book of prayers he wrote was stored in the Edgeville Monastery, so you will need to go there and retrieve it. And quickly!
* '''Brother Tranquility:''' Here, I'll take you straight back to Mos Le'Harmless.
* {{qact|Brother Tranquility teleports the player back to Harmony Island.}}
* {{tact|end}}

